  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for xwayland",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for xwayland fixes the following issues\n\n- CVE-2026-55999: missing bounds check in `glamor_font_get` can lead to a heap buffer overflow when a font loaded from\n  a malicious PCF file is processed (bsc#1268893).\n- CVE-2026-56000: improper memory management in `CommonMakeCurrent` can lead to a heap use-after-free when an\n  interaction with a malicious client creating GLX contexts happens (bsc#1268894).\n  ",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
